         <div type="translation" source="#irt2009" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">In honour</supplied> of Esperius, splendid man <supplied reason="explanation">of senatorial status</supplied>. To Decimius Esperius, splendid man <supplied reason="explanation">of senatorial status</supplied>, former proconsul of the province of Africa, a juryman in the imperial court, of an office-holding family, moreover a man increasing <note>in dignity</note> stage by stage and through the fame won ?on account of the justice which he displayed in the case of the Tripolitanians which was referred to the emperor as judge. To an outstanding patron, the city council of Lepcis Magna, alwauys his client, together with the people, erected <supplied reason="subaudible">this</supplied>.</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>ll. 1, 2. Decimius Hilarianus Hesperius, <title level="m">PW</title> VIII, 1249, 1; son of Ausonius the poet, proconsul of Africa in 376. </p>
